cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on investigating the performance of low-latency applications in wireless networks, which is a key area of research in networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses the effective capacity (EC) model, which is a link-layer channel model with QoS-awareness, to investigate the performance of wireless networks under certain statistical delay constraints. This is a key area of research in information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper specifically mentions multimedia communications as one of the low-latency applications for next-generation wireless networks, indicating a focus on multimedia. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper mentions cognitive radio networks (CRNs) as one of the wireless networks where the EC model has been used, indicating a focus on security and cryptography in wireless networks. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper mentions adhoc networks and mesh networks as two of the wireless networks where the EC model has been used, indicating a focus on data structures and algorithms for wireless networks.
